85). Editors: F.D. Parker and J.T. Burgett, <June 13-July 18, 1885; J.Q. Adams, <March 5, 1887-December 29, 1888>. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 2 (June 13, 1885); title from PDF masthead (Readex America's Historical Newspapers Web site, viewed June 18, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. IV, no. 31 (December 29, 1888) (viewed June 18, 2013). Appeal (Saint Paul, Minn.) 2769-3139 (DLC) 2011254040 (OCoLC)664616804"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:15.066Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013254362/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["minneapolis", "illinois", "ramsey", "minnesota", "hennepin", "saint paul", "cook", "united states", "chicago"], "number": ["2013254362", "732734928", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2011254040", "online resource", "2769-3120"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "western appeal (st. paul, minn.;st. paul and minneapolis, minn.;st. paul & minneapolis, minn.) 1885-18?? [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 121.78398, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD AN", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["minneapolis", "illinois", "minnesota", "ramsey", "minneapolis (minn.)", "hennepin", "saint paul", "newspapers", "saint paul (minn.)", "united states", "cook", "african american", "african american newspapers", "chicago (ill.)", "chicago", "african americans"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:48:57.173Z", "title": "Western appeal", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013254362/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016811/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83016811", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/caeb13f9-27c1-5f3c-b24e-e39d3f575cf7"], "batch": ["mnhi_effie_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["parker, f.d.", "adams, john quincy", "burge